Show HN: The Philosopher from Carnival Island (HTML)
text:
I wrote a book about absolute nothingness, or at least alluded to its omnipresence, and uploaded it to a fun, somewhat formatted static site for free.

I think when I wrote it I wanted someone to discuss it with, but I’ve since realised it’s a very boring topic to many, and still most get offended by the mere challenging of their beliefs.

It’s not to say I am certain what this book says is correct, but that I would love to understand another’s point of view of… well, nothing at all.

I’ve been a little too obsessed with this concept for a few years now, and don’t regret writing the book, but can’t help but think I could have had a few more discussion if I wrote about, literally, anything else (that isn’t nothing)
